               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;This fragment contains part of the thirteenth act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka; an Uy. parallel is MaitrHami XIII, 9a19-10a15f. See also [[Pinault 1999]]: 201.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b7.&lt;/b&gt; Ilya Itkin (p.c., 20 July 2016) suggests restoring &lt;i&gt;(sä)rk&lt;/i&gt;, which is supported by the fact that the expression "sickness, old age and death" is also attested in [[YQ I.10]] a6, albeit with the word [[wraske]] for "sickness" instead of [[särk]]. On the other hand, the restoration &lt;i&gt;(sä)rk&lt;/i&gt; conflicts with the Uyghur translation, which only mentions old age and death: &lt;i&gt;qarïmaq ölmäkn(i)ng&lt;/i&gt; (MaitrHami XIII, 10a13, cf. [[Geng et al. 1991]]: 280).&lt;/p&gt;</item>
